<title>USA: AFTER THE BELL - Stocks trade lightly.</title>
<headline>AFTER THE BELL - Stocks trade lightly.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-05-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>U.S. stocks were trading mixed in the after-hours session following the release of quarterly earnings by a variety of companies, dealers said Thursday.</p>
<p>&quot;There was some activity,&quot; said one trader.</p>
<p>W.R. Berkley Corp was down to 48-13/16 against a Nasdaq Stock Market close of 49-1/8 and OrthoLogic Corp was at 5-13/16 against a close of 5-7/8.</p>
<p>Platinum Technology Inc was down at 12-1/4 from 12-1/2 and Visioneer Inc was at 3-7/16 against 3-3/8.</p>
<p>Most of them released earnings reports after normal trading hours.  </p>
<p>The New York Stock Exchange said Thursday session one had a small volume of 500 shares compared to 25,500 the previous day. Session two had 1.0 million against 6.7 million, it said.</p>
